version_description:
Brand new features within Auto! Until now, tapping Auto applied Smooth, Whiten and Details where needed. It now includes Glow, Conceal, Cleanse, Cool Down and Fix Shadow for a complete quick fix!

How can we make Facetune better? Is there a tool you NEED that we haven't added yet?
VIP users can now send feature requests directly from within the app! Get in touch with us - we can't wait to hear from you.

We've got a lot of new stuff for you in this update!
- There's a new Apply button within Patch to make your workflow easier. Now you can apply as many "patches" as you want without having to leave Patch and go back in.
- We've created a Contour & Highlight tutorial in the Paint help section. Find it by tapping the [?] icon in the top left corner within Paint.
- Get creative with the new colors we've added in the Paint brush & Tone brush color palettes.
- We've renamed Facetune-edited photos to include their original name when imported to other platforms. This will make finding and organizing them easier on you.
- Due to overwhelming user requests, photos shot with the Facetune camera are no longer mirrored! You can always revert back in the Settings menu.
- Added Filter pack: Belle!

Enjoy!
Daniel & The Facetune Team

P.S. If you love Facetune, we'd be so very thankful if you rated us. Ratings do get reset with updates, so every bit helps!

Here’s what’s new in this update!

- Custom Backdrop! Our #1 user-requested feature! You can now use any photo in your camera roll as a Backdrop.
- Better layout! We've made a few small changes to bring you a more streamlined workflow that will make retouching faster and simpler. You can now find Retouch, Filters and all your Tools in one toolbar for easy access!
- We're all ready for the new iPhone X! We've made some backstage changes in preparation for the next generation of Apple devices and we're excited to see the gorgeous portraits you create when you pair the power of Facetune with the new iPhone X.

Enjoy!
Daniel & The Facetune Team
